Sketchbook in folder captioned: Bow wave; London; hens of Aran
Contains sketches of Fitzgerald's travels in the Aran Islands, Ireland, including coastal scenes, portraits of people, hands gripping oars, and Irish chickens and cows. Also includes a few sketches of Big Ben in London and landscapes from Monhegan Island, Maine.
Archives of American Art, Smithsonian Institution
